The paper deals with computer vision tasks, specifically visual tracking, and proposes a method that involves pre-training a convolutional neural network (CNN) offline and then transferring the learned feature hierarchies to online tracking. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves machine learning techniques such as pre-training and fine-tuning a CNN, which are commonly used in the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with image and video processing, which are relevant to the sub-categories of Multimedia (cs.MM) and Robotics (cs.RO).
